Package gov.nasa.worldwind.formats.dds

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ColorBlockExtractor
    The ColorBlockExtrator interface will copy a 4x4 block of pixel data from an image source.
    DXTCompressor
    The DXTCompressor interface will compress an in-memory image using one of the DXT block compression schemes.
    DXTDecompressor  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AlphaBlockDXT3
    AlphaBlockDXT3 is a data structure representing the compressed alpha values in a single DXT2/DXT3 block.
    BasicColorBlockExtractor
    Provides access to 4x4 blocks of pixel data from a BufferedImage via the ColorBlockExtractor interface.
    BlockDXT1
    BlockDXT1 is a data structure representing the compressed color values in a single 64 bit DXT1 block.
    BlockDXT1Compressor
    Compressor for DXT1 color blocks.
    BlockDXT3
    BlockDXT3 is a data structure representing the compressed alpha and color values in a single DXT2/DXT3 block.
    BlockDXT3Compressor
    Compressor for DXT2/DXT3 alpha and color blocks.
    Color24
    24 bit 888 RGB color
    Color32
    32 bit 8888 ARGB color.
    ColorBlock4x4
    Uncompressed 4x4 color block.
    DDSCompressor
    DDSCompressor converts in-memory images into a DDS file encoded with one of the DXT block compression algorithms.
    DDSConstants
    Documentation on Direct3D format constants is available at http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb172558(VS.85).aspx.
    DDSDecompressor  
    DDSHeader
    Documentation on the DDS header format is available at http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb943982(VS.85).aspx
    DDSPixelFormat
    Documentation on the DDS pixel format is available at http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb943982(VS.85).aspx
    DXT1Compressor  
    DXT1Decompressor  
    DXT3Compressor  
    DXT3Decompressor  
    DXTCompressionAttributes  
    StandaloneDDSConverter
